---
title: Penne Arrabbiata with Pancetta, Chili, and Parmesan
description: Translating to “angry” in Italian, arrabbiata is known for its kick. We’ve reinvented this Italian classic by adding salty pancetta to the mix. Wilting arugula into the sauce is a great way to sneak in extra greens. If you’re not a fan of heat, simply leave out the chili pepper!
